result.execSummary:
The defendant Emmanuel Dontell Higgins was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. On one or more other charges, Emmanuel Dontell Higgins was found not guilty. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Emmanuel Dontell Higgins is presumed innocent of the not guilty charges.

  • Emmanuel Dontell Higgins was found guilty of Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Emmanuel Dontell Higgins was found guilty of Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Defendant Emmanuel Dontell Higgins in court with attorney Gregg H. Novack.  Defendant Emmanuel Dontell Higgins in custody.  Megan Marie Williamson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing proceeds.  State has complied with victim notification.  Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant. COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms, he must provide a DNA sample and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  

As to Count 4:
COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE -  6 years with Zero days credit consecutive to any other sentence -  INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -  4 years  -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION -  2 years

As to Count 6:
COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE -  6 years with Zero days credit consecutive to the sentence imposed as to Count 4;-  INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -  4 years  -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION -  2 years

Court finds defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program - after 7 years of confinement has been served.

As to both counts:

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
- Mental Health evaluation and any recommended treatment
- AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
- Absolute Sobriety
- Random Screens
- No drugs without a valid prescription
- No association with illegal drugs, drug houses, drug dealers, drug paraphernalia
- Cognitive Thinking/Behavior
- Participate in any other programs or treatment recommended by the agent
- Obtain GED/HSD
- Seek/Maintain full-time employment
- No fine
- No Contact with the co-actor
- No Contact with the victims - Andrew C., Gail P., Kevin D.  AND/OR  Brian M.
- Pay Restitution in the amount of $800 to Kevin Driscoll
- Pay restitution, costs, fees, assessments and surcharges during the term of extended supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis - as to Count 4
-  DOC to collect monetary sums/amounts at the rate of 25% of prison funds.

Appeal rights given.  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence, Pretrial Incarceration Credit and Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief and Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgment received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.
